<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Glabrous perennial herb with trailing or twining stems up to 2 m long. Leaves petiolate, 2.5-7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-5 cm, deltoid, acute to acuminate, margin entire, base cordate but not cuneate onto the petiole, auriculate with auricles weakly 2 (- 3)-lobed, with one lobe larger than the other; petioles 0.5-4.5 cm long. Flowers 1-5 in pedunculate axillary cymes; peduncles 3.5-16 cm long; bracteoles 3-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1 mm, linear to linear-lanceolate, acute; pedicels 8-11 mm, so inflorescence rather dense; outer sepals 6-7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
5 mm, broadly oblong-obovate to rectangular, truncate and minutely mucronate, glabrous, scarious; inner sepals 7-11 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
4.5-6 mm; corolla 3-4 cm, pale yellow, undulate, midpetaline bands glabrous except for a few hairs near the apex; filaments with sessile glands below; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided 11-15 mm above the base, stigmas 3 mm. Capsule glabrous; seeds smooth (especially in Iraq) to tuberculate. [
<bibRefCitation author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
